>
> I recently purchased an otherwise amazing condition HF100-G, with the
> exception that someone thought Barn Red paint looked batter on it than its
> original "Silver Zebrano Plastic Veneer." I disagree. This new acquisition
> prompts me to want to find out if anyone has ever restored any of these
> Seeburgs to look factory original. The HF100-R "Bleached Mahogany", M100C
> "Blonde and Lime", and 100J "Woven Cane and Red Mahogany Plastic Veneer"
> also immediately come to mind.
